   307 				;==========================================================================
   308 				; FASC [D8E6]		Floating Point to ASCII conversion
   309 				;
   310 				; Converts an FP number in FR0 to an ASCII representation in LBUFF, setting
   311 				; INBUFF to the start of the string and with bit 7 set on the last
   312 				; character.
   313 				;
   314 				; Negative values are preceded by '-', followed by at least one decimal
   315 				; digit -- so values smaller than 1.0 in magnitude start with "0.".
   316 				; Exponential notation is used for values <0.01 or >=10^10, with the
   317 				; form m.mmmmmmmmE+nn; trailing zeroes on the mantissa are trimmed, along
   318 				; with the . if there are no non-zero digits after it.
   319 				;
   320 				; Quirks:
   321 				;	- INBUFF can actually point a couple of characters below LBUFF in some
   322 				;	  cases. We do similar for negative numbers, but we don't precisely
   323 				;	  emulate the exact INBUFF values.
   324 				;	- One decimal digit is always printed for odd exponents, but not for
   325 				;	  even exponents, e.g. 1E+10 and 1.0E+11.
   326 				;
   327 D8E5					fixadr	$d8e6
